---

BOBYQA (Bound Optimization BY Quadratic Approximation)

  Original algorithm by M.J.D. Powell (2009).
  "The BOBYQA algorithm for bound constrained optimization without
  derivatives." Cambridge NA Report NA2009/06, University of Cambridge.

  Ported to Rust from the Java implementation in Apache Commons Math 3.6.1,
  which is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
  https://commons.apache.org/proper/commons-math/

---

DIRECT-C (DIviding RECTangles — locally biased variant)

  Original DIRECT algorithm by D.R. Jones, C.D. Perttunen, and
  B.E. Stuckman (1993). "Lipschitzian optimization without the Lipschitz
  constant." Journal of Optimization Theory and Applications, 79(1):157-181.

  Locally biased DIRECT-L variant by J.M. Gablonsky and C.T. Kelley (2001).
  "A locally-biased form of the DIRECT algorithm." Journal of Global
  Optimization, 21(1):27-37.

  Implementation references:
  - NLopt library by Steven G. Johnson (MIT License) for the base DIRECT
    algorithm structure.
  - WIDesigner v2.6.0 (GPL v3) for the algorithmic description of the
    DIRECT-C variant (locally biased selection with constraint handling).

  The Rust code in this project is original work, not a translation of
  either NLopt or WIDesigner source code.

---

CIPM-2007 Air Properties Model

  Speed of sound, density, viscosity, and thermal conductivity of moist air
  computed from the CIPM-2007 equation (published scientific standard by the
  International Committee for Weights and Measures). Not copyrightable.

---

Acoustic Transfer Matrix Method

  Standard textbook method for computing impedance of cylindrical and
  conical waveguides. Based on published acoustic physics literature.

